Articles.Content:
> 1. Would it be possible to alter the <crew> element to not include the situational text (e.g. Jebediah landed on Minmus), I'm already using custom situational text and the repetition is unneeded</crew>

Actually looking at this myself in your Git repo, I think all you'd need to do is replace this section of Text.cs to add a new <crew-> option that would exclude the situation text:</crew->

    if (text.Contains("") || text.Contains("")){    var value = "";    if (vessel != null)    {        if (vessel.GetCrewCount() > 0)        {            value = string.Join(", ", vessel.GetVesselCrew().Select(item => item.name).ToArray());        }        else        {            if (vessel.isCommandable)            {                value = "Unmanned";            }            else            {                value = "N/A";            }        }    }    text = text.Replace("", value + " " + Vessel.GetSituationString(vessel));    text = text.Replace("", value);}
